 Usage instructions

Installs software for MySQL 5.6 Enterprise x64 edition on RedHat Linux 6.  This includes the server, client files, and any other optional components included in RPM files.


 Dependencies

SElinux must be turned off.
RPM files must be mounted locally, available through an external download server, or a combination of the two.


 Results verification

Run "ps aux | grep mysql" to ensure that mysql process is running after the workflow successfully completes
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    List of RPMs - Comma-delimited list of RPMs that are either sitting in staging directory or will need to be downloaded from software repository
    Server.Become Routine - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Template File - *Optional - A template file to be used for custom configurations.
    Staging Directory - *Optional\: Fully qualified path of the directory where mysql installer will be downloaded to. Will be cleaned up at end of workflow execution.  Default /tmp/mysql_stage will be created if no input provided.
    MySQL Root Password - *Optional - Password for the MySQL user
    Backup Zipfile - *Optional - ZIP file to be used for installing the backup utility.
